      	  <h2>Steve Lambsden</h2>
            <h3>Lead Vocals and Guitar</h3>
            <p>Steve reckons he is a bit of a motorcycle fan, well he has to move his bike out to get into his music studio, and it always seems to spend more time out than in! As a teenager Steve found a musical outlet in the bass guitar, he still has his little Fender Mustang from back in the day. Since then he has expanded, not only into singing and guitar, but in his self-built studio where he plays drums, keys andeven a synth sax!</p>
            <p>His roots are in electric blues - Peter Green, Santana, Clapton, BB King and the Allmans but Steve also has a good ear for music generally, leading him to getting involved in a variety of interesting recording projects in his studio. He has not only written all of the original songs on the band’s album but recorded, engineered and produced them too.</p>
            <p>Steve has the most expensive taste in instruments; he uses a PRS Santana guitar (which goes through a variety of funny little tins with flashing lights and knobs) the glorious sound of which emerges in all its magnificence from a Mesa Boogie Lone Star Special combo amp.</p>
            <p>Fave BI Song - Everything But Love</p>         
