          <h2>Tony Elsworth-Smith</h2>
          <h3>Harp &amp; Occasional Vox</h3>
          <p>It was seeing the live rocking blues of bands like George Thorogood and The Destroyers and The Fabulous Thunderbirds at legendary London venues Dingwall’s and Hope &amp; Anchor back in the 80’s &amp; 90’s that pressed the button for Tony; and a friend’s birthday that gave him the excuse to get a band together. ‘The Bridge’ was born – a 10 piece Soul band!</p>
          <p>Influences? from the great Kim Wilson (harp, of course) to Augustus Pablo (Dub melodica), Paul Butterfield, the two Walters, the Sonny Boys… please, don’t start him talking, it’s a long list!</p>
          <p>In 2002 Tony was given Steve Lambsden’s number by his barber - The Blues Issue was born.</p>
          <p>Tony insists on Hohner Marine Band harps, is rather fond of his Harpgear Double Trouble amp from the U.S. as well as his selection of vintage harp mics…and his own very long vintage tweed lead!</p>
          <p>Fave BI tune - Hoochie Coochie Man</p>      
