   	    <h2>Nodd</h2>
        <h3>Basses and occasional B.Vox</h3>
        <p>“Talent spotted” at a jam night in Hove, Nodd first appeared with the ‘Stan’s Blue Notes’ version of BI in 2004, and got fired 3 months later…oops! Clerical error. Shortly after this false start he was re-instated and has held down the bottom end of BI business since.</p>
        <p>On his way to Worthing Nodd enjoyed a period of success with Glasgow band “The Radars”, a publishing contract with Slade, 10 years of 50’s style R’n’B with “5 Go Jazz” and a hit track on a Ministry of Sound album. In addition to his Blues duties, Nodd also supplies low-end energy to Cajun band “Rough Chowder” as well as Simon Beavis’ mellifluous folk.</p>
        <p>Outside of his music, Nodd produces and manages several large festivals and events, both in the UK and abroad and he reads comics, lots of them!</p>
        <p>Bass underpinning is maintained using a ‘75 Fender Precision, Musicman Bongo or Dean EUB (all lefties) into a Mesa Boogie Walkabout amp, EAW and Mesa Scout speakers, in addition to an almost limitless number of facial contortions and strutting.</p>
        <p>Fave BI Groove - Ramblin’ Blues</p>
