      	  <h2>Glenn Mc Pheat</h2>
          <h3>Guitar &amp; Sometime Lead Vox</h3>
          <p>He’s been playing since school days and still does - he’s a teacher! From jamming Hendrix with a classmate on melodean, Glen has an impressive track record ranging across folk, pop, blues and rock’n’roll, other influences include Zep, Muddy Waters and Lou Reed. It was his stint together with Nodd in a Cajun band that introduced him to BI.</p>
          <p>His upfront style supplies many a scorching riff, although once a fiery solo saw him set his hair alight. Glen also heads up “The Shakedown Collective” a four-piece band which includes his brother..and Matt.</p>
          <p>In his other life, quieter contemplation and natural things bring balance to his character…just don’t mention packing the gear away!</p>
          <p>Glen strums his favourite Tokai DC Love Rock guitar thro a Zen Overdrive, TC Electronics Hall of Fame Reverb and Spark pedals into an Evil Robot combo amplifier, well, this week at least, watch this space for new guitars and effects - it won’t be long.</p>
          <p>Fave BI Song - Whipping Post</p>        
