      	  <h2>Matt Greenfield</h2>
          <h3>Drums</h3>
          <p>Spending most of his working hours in front of a computer, Matt ensures his unique life/work balance by film-making and cycling… doesn’t he fall off? His comparatively brief but busy musical career has seen him play Mustang Sally in almost every workingmen’s club on the South Coast, his dead pan ‘drum face’ belies the enthusiasm and joy he brings to his performances. He also reduces the average age of the band by 20%.</p>
          <p>Sticksmen he admire include Steve Jordan, Carter Beauford and ?uestlove and for the Blues – Ray Charles, John Mayer &amp; Derek Trucks.</p>
          <p>Matt also holds the drummer’s position in Glen’s own band “Shakedown Project” and a “function band”.</p>
          <p>Matt rocks a 1962 Ludwig Super Classic drum kit with a Yamaha ‘Steve Jordan Signature’ 13” x 6.5” Snare, he uses Zildjian K and A cymbals all of which he wallops with Vic Firth sticks.</p>
